# ThaiPass Project Rules

## Brand

- Brand name is always **ThaiPass** (never ThaiVisa Pro or generic «агентство виз»).
- Tone: premium, calm, expert relocation service — not budget visa shop.
- UI language: Russian. SEO locale: `ru-RU`. Primary geo: Russia, Moscow.

## Services (client-facing names)

| Slug | Name |
|------|------|
| `dtv-audit` | ThaiPass DTV Audit |
| `dtv-concierge` | ThaiPass DTV Concierge |
| `tr-express` | ThaiPass TR Express |
| `tr-standard` | ThaiPass TR Standard |
| `retirement-50` | ThaiPass Retirement Path |

Never use «вариант 1/2» in user-facing copy.

## Stack

- **Next.js 15** App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4
- **React Bits** + **Magic UI** for motion (phase 2+)
- **shadcn/ui** for forms, accordion, dialog
- **WordPress REST API** for blog (`/blog`)
- **Context7** MCP for Next.js/React docs when writing code

## Content strategy (70 / 20 / 10)

- **70%** pain, objections, scenarios, FAQ-as-objections on landing
- **20%** product: packages, quiz, process, delivery
- **10%** trust: Moscow office, courier, Telegram channel — minimal «about us»

## Contacts

- Primary CTA: **lead form** → Telegram notification
- Secondary: WhatsApp, Telegram channel (news/prices)
- **No phone number** on site until operator and number are ready

## Workflow phases

1. **Phase 1**: functionality — routing, form API, blog fetch, base layout
2. **Phase 2**: content + SEO meta, Schema.org, semantic core briefs
3. **Phase 3**: Aura `AURADESIGN.md`, React Bits motion, Magic UI components

## MCP tools

- **ЯДрышко** (`/core`): semantic core, Wordstat via MCP-KV
- **Aura Designer**: `auradesign/AURADESIGN.md`
- **IndexLift SEO**: audit after pages are built
- **Browser DevTools MCP**: verify UI changes before marking complete

## YMYL disclaimer

Every page footer must state ThaiPass is not a government body. Link to [thaievisa.go.th](https://www.thaievisa.go.th) and [moscow.thaiembassy.org](https://moscow.thaiembassy.org). Show «Актуально на [month] 2026» on visa content.

## Code

- Minimize scope; match existing patterns in `apps/web`
- Use `apps/web` as the Next.js root
- Env secrets only in `.env`, never commit `.env`
